 },
 {
  "text": "And feedback from the managers?",
  "voice": "arthur",
  "file": "a17_and_feedback_from_the_managers.mp3"
 },
 {
  "text": "We received numerous comments. The bulk of them ask for more staff.",
  "voice": "ellen",
  "file": "a17_we_received_numerous_comments_the_bulk_of_them_a.mp3"
 },
 {
  "text": "There is too much overtime.",
  "voice": "arthur",
  "file": "a17_there_is_too_much_overtime.mp3"
 },
 {
  "text": "We have enough data to decide.",
  "voice": "ellen",
  "file": "a17_we_have_enough_data_to_decide.mp3"
 },
 {
  "text": "Good morning. Let me review our staffing numbers. We have many open roles this quarter, but not enough recruiters to fill them. There is too much overtime, and morale is low. We received numerous applications, yet only a handful are qualified. Skilled talent is scarce, and our budget is minimal. Still, we have plenty of internal candidates, and we have sufficient data to plan well. The bulk of our effort will go to the busiest teams. With a little patience, I am confident we will close most of the roles.",
  "voice": "arthur",
  "file": "a17_listening_staffing.mp3"
 },
 {
  "text": "Hello team. Let me talk about the budget. We do not have much money this year; the increase was minimal. We have a few priorities, so we must spend carefully. There is a surplus of low-priority requests, but insufficient funds for all of them. The bulk of the budget goes to salaries, and only a little is left for training. We have ample data to guide our choices, and plenty of good ideas. If we focus on a few key areas, we will have enough to make a real difference. Thank you.",
  "voice": "ellen",
  "file": "a17_listening_budget.mp3"
 },
